Nand is a simple game — you can hold left to go left, OR hold right to go right, OR don’t press any side and automatically return to the center. That’s why it’s called Nand — because you can press left, or right, or nothing, but never both sides at the same time.The idea is to keep going further down — infinitely. After every 10 points, the outline of the main triangle changes, the speed of the blocks increases, and the insignias on the game over screen also change. You can cycle through the 7 colors of the rainbow, unlocking a new one every 10 points.

Fancy seeing a pair of kiwi brawling in your garden! That's the sight that Kerikeri local Karin Matthews saw last week when she herd some strange noises coming from outside. We think the birds may have been fighting over food - and possibly coming out during the day to find food. Conditions are currently very dry in Northland at the moment which makes it much harder than normal for kiwi to forage for food. When the ground is hard and dry, they find it hard to probe into the ground to find food. And if they can't feed enough at night when they should be out and about, they have to try to feed during the day as well. Read the full story here >>> https://ow.ly/YrEQ50VsRNW 📷: Karin Matthews & One News #savethekiwi #kiwisaver

⚡𝗘𝗹𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗦𝗮𝗳𝗲𝘁𝘆 in 𝗠𝗲𝗱𝗶𝘂𝗺 𝗩𝗼𝗹𝘁𝗮𝗴𝗲 switchgears is a bit different animal than in Low Voltage. I saw this video few times and I think it should go further. No or little injuries happen, luckily. However it is important to discuss what went good ,what went bad and what we can learn from this. 𝗙𝗲𝘄 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀 : 🔸 it is 6000 VAC HV switchgear (old one)  🔸 activity - rolling/sliding in HV breaker into panel 🔸 reason for arc flash explosion is not clear 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝘄𝗲 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗹𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗻 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀: 🔹 always have&follow procedures (this should be part of Electrical Safety Plan)  🔹 we need hazard and risk assessment (in UK RAMS for example) 🔹 we need proper PPE selection (both shock and arc flash) against task and hazard we calculated 𝗔𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗲𝘄 𝗼𝗳 𝗺𝘆 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗲𝘀 𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲: - 𝟮 𝘀𝗲𝗰 𝗿𝘂𝗹𝗲 𝗶𝗻 𝗡𝗙𝗣𝗔𝟳𝟬𝗘 - here You can see how it works if someone can escape in time  - 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝘁𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘀𝗲𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴s - this fault escalated quickly but nothing trips for +20 seconds so protection needs to be reviewed &retested to see why ? - 𝘀𝘂𝗯𝘀𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗱𝗮𝗺𝗮𝗴𝗲 - as we see it will need to be replaced most likely  - 𝘂𝗽𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗺 𝘀𝘂𝗯𝘀𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 damage - what we don't see is substation above this one which was under fault stress (in this case arc flash current) and nothing is fault rated >3sec so it will require big review and resting - 𝗣𝗣𝗘 - it is interesting topic as they actually wear complete PPE (balaclava, helmet with faceshield, hand gloves, and full PPE set) - question only if it wa selected against thermal hazard ( Incident energy) or very lucky guess 🤔 𝗦𝗽𝗮𝗿𝗸 𝗦𝗮𝗳𝗲𝘁𝘆 #electricalengineering #electricalsafety #arcflash #substation

In 1981, Diego Maradona was a rising football star playing for Boca Juniors in Argentina. At just 21 years old, he was already considered one of the best players in the world due to his exceptional dribbling, vision, and goal-scoring ability. That year, he helped Boca Juniors win the Argentine Primera División Metropolitano title, marking his first major club trophy. His performances led to a world-record transfer to FC Barcelona in 1982. Meanwhile, Pelé had already retired from professional football by 1981. The Brazilian legend had played his last official match in 1977 with the New York Cosmos. However, he remained an influential figure in the sport, often making public appearances and promoting football globally. By that time, he had won three FIFA World Cups (1958, 1962, 1970) and was widely regarded as one of the greatest players in history. In 1981, Maradona and Pelé met for an iconic joint interview, where Pelé advised Maradona on handling fame and pressure. This was a historic moment, symbolizing the transition between two footballing eras.

China, South Korea, and Japan have agreed to jointly counter U.S. President Donald Trump’s tariffs, following a trilateral economic dialogue in Seoul. The first such meeting in five years, it involved trade ministers Ahn Duk-geun (South Korea), Yoji Muto (Japan), and Wang Wentao (China). They pledged to strengthen regional trade and expedite a trilateral free trade agreement, aiming for a “free, fair, and mutually beneficial” framework. The move responds to Trump’s 25% tariffs on Asian car exports and broader levies on steel and aluminum, reflecting a strategic push against U.S. trade policies.

周函德 sent an attachment.
People aren’t wired for critical thinking. Their decisions mostly revolve around avoiding social ostracization. If being “masculine” is in fashion, men will conform to it. If blaming a certain group is normalized, people will follow suit. If drinking coffee is the standard, they’ll keep drinking it—even if it’s bad for them. At its core, human reasoning is primarily a tool for social inclusion, not objective analysis. I focus on aligning my thinking with logic, specifically in relation to natural laws. If the sun is out, I reason that animals have evolved under consistent sun exposure, so it makes sense for me to get a certain amount as well. If caffeine is widely consumed, I question why I’d drink it, whether animals historically had access to it, and if it disrupts a natural equilibrium in my physiology. When I see people loading heavy barbells onto their backs, I assess whether their joints are functionally rebounding against that force or if the movement is structurally compromising them. What I don’t do… I don’t determine my actions based on whether people think something is “cool” or socially acceptable. Instead, I establish sound first principles, then use science and my own direct observations to evaluate whether a behavior will benefit my biology. I don’t know if most people process information the way I do, but this approach works. And when something works, I don’t need validation for it—I let the results speak for themselves.

Lisa Piccirillo is an American mathematician known for solving a decades-old problem in knot theory. In 2020, she proved that the Conway knot—a knot discovered in 1970—was not slice, meaning it couldn’t bound a smooth disk in four-dimensional space. This was a major breakthrough, especially since the problem had remained unsolved for 50 years. What makes her story even more remarkable? She solved it in just a week while she was a graduate student at the University of Texas at Austin. Her work quickly gained recognition, earning her a position as an assistant professor at MIT even before she finished her PhD. Her achievement showcases the power of fresh perspectives in mathematics and highlights the importance of perseverance in problem-solving. #Mathematics #Mathematician #physics #chemistry#STEM #WomenInSTEM #Math #PureMath #QuantFinance #ProblemSolving #MIT #AcademicLife #collage #stockmarket #wallstreet#math#university #research #jee #hft #hedgefund #jimsimons #iit#mit#PHD#calculus #algorithmictrading #engineering #cs

有兩個模型，一個是老師另一個是學生
Feb 17, 2025 8:56 am
吳柏翰
大致就是
Feb 17, 2025 8:56 am
吳柏翰
你提到 「老師模型」（Teacher Model） 和 「學生模型」（Student Model），這是正確的！👍 這個過程的關鍵步驟就是：
1️⃣ 使用老師模型產生大量的問答對（問題 + 老師的回答）。
2️⃣ 學生模型學習老師模型的輸出，試圖模仿老師的回答方式。
3️⃣ 最後，學生模型可以產生與老師相似的回答，但計算資源需求更少。

這個方法確實是知識蒸餾（Knowledge Distillation） 的核心概念！🔥


---

🔹 你的回答可以加強的地方

你的回答雖然簡單易懂，但有幾點可以再補充，使概念更精準：

✅ 學生模型不只是模仿答案，而是學習「老師的內部邏輯」

除了直接學習老師的輸出，學生模型還會學習老師模型對於不同輸入的「機率分布」，讓它能更好地理解不同類型的問題，而不只是單純記憶答案。


✅ 蒸餾的關鍵：軟標籤（Soft Labels）

傳統機器學習通常是「對或錯」的分類（硬標籤），但蒸餾過程會使用老師模型的機率分布作為學習目標，這讓學生模型學習更多細節。例如：

老師模型可能輸出：「貓 🐱」的機率 80%、「狐狸 🦊」的機率 15%、「狗 🐶」的機率 5%。

學生模型學習時，不只是學「這是貓」，還會學「為什麼它像貓，但又有一點像狐狸？」



✅ 學生模型通常比老師模型小，但保留大部分能力

透過蒸餾，小模型可以在效能下降不多的情況下，大幅減少計算資源需求，這對於手機、IoT 設備等低資源環境很有幫助！📱



---

🔹 總結

你的回答 基本上是正確的，但如果你想要解釋得更完整，可以提到：
✔ 學生模型不只是「背答案」，而是學習老師的內部邏輯。
✔ 蒸餾過程會使用「軟標籤」（機率分布）來幫助學生學得更好。
✔ 透過蒸餾，小模型可以變快又節省資源，這在應用上很重要！

如果對方只是一般人，你的簡單版回答已經夠用了，但如果是跟 AI 相關的人聊，可以加這些細節，讓解釋更專業！😆🚀

吳柏翰
我今天去面試的時候被問到這題，「模型的蒸餾到底是什麼？」
  • 😮周函德
Feb 12, 2025 8:37 am
吳柏翰
🔹 你的回答的核心概念

你提到 「老師模型」（Teacher Model） 和 「學生模型」（Student Model），這是正確的！👍 這個過程的關鍵步驟就是：
1️⃣ 使用老師模型產生大量的問答對（問題 + 老師的回答）。
2️⃣ 學生模型學習老師模型的輸出，試圖模仿老師的回答方式。
3️⃣ 最後，學生模型可以產生與老師相似的回答，但計算資源需求更少。

這個方法確實是知識蒸餾（Knowledge Distillation） 的核心概念！🔥


---

🔹 你的回答可以加強的地方

你的回答雖然簡單易懂，但有幾點可以再補充，使概念更精準：

✅ 學生模型不只是模仿答案，而是學習「老師的內部邏輯」

除了直接學習老師的輸出，學生模型還會學習老師模型對於不同輸入的「機率分布」，讓它能更好地理解不同類型的問題，而不只是單純記憶答案。


✅ 蒸餾的關鍵：軟標籤（Soft Labels）

傳統機器學習通常是「對或錯」的分類（硬標籤），但蒸餾過程會使用老師模型的機率分布作為學習目標，這讓學生模型學習更多細節。例如：

老師模型可能輸出：「貓 🐱」的機率 80%、「狐狸 🦊」的機率 15%、「狗 🐶」的機率 5%。

學生模型學習時，不只是學「這是貓」，還會學「為什麼它像貓，但又有一點像狐狸？」



✅ 學生模型通常比老師模型小，但保留大部分能力

透過蒸餾，小模型可以在效能下降不多的情況下，大幅減少計算資源需求，這對於手機、IoT 設備等低資源環境很有幫助！📱

長庚醫院分享給大家的
炒蛋禁忌 ：

再一次提醒⋯⋯

⚫️聽過「醬油蛋」，沒有聽過「鹽 巴蛋」。

⚫️蛋汁中不可加入「鹽巴」, 這是很重要的觀念 。

⚫️炒蛋 或 蒸蛋時，不可先在蛋汁中加入鹽巴。
因為鹽與蛋中的乳酸菌結合，會產生「氯」，有毒 ！

⚫️所以⋯⋯蒸蛋就只 能加醬油 。

⚫️若加鹽蒸的蛋，蛋白會有一點綠綠的顏色。
那就是化學變化產生的氯。

◾️炒蛋，你就等起鍋前再加鹽吧！

⚫️記住：為了大家的健康，
告訴週遭「會進廚房的人 。

🇬🇧 The Intel 80286 is a 16-bit CISC microprocessor manufactured by Intel and launched on 1 February 1982. It is the successor to the Intel 8086 and the predecessor of the Intel 80386, which I have already described. It was released at the same time as the Intel 80186, and initially clocked at 6 and 8 MHz, its frequency was increased to 25 MHz. It was widely used in compatible PCs from the mid-1980s to the early 1990s. The Siemens SAB 80286-R was clocked at 10 MHz. This processor also dates from 1982, so how old were your parents in 1982 ? 🇫🇷 L’Intel 80286, est un microprocesseur CISC 16 bits fabriqué par Intel et présenté le 1er février 1982. C’est le successeur de l’Intel 8086 et le prédécesseur de l’Intel 80386 que j’ai déjà présenté. Il est sorti en même temps que l’Intel 80186. Initialement cadencé à 6 et 8 MHz, sa fréquence augmenta jusqu’à 25 MHz. Il était alors très utilisé dans les compatibles PC du milieu des années 1980 au début des années 1990. Le Siemens SAB 80286-R était cadencé à 10 MHz Ce processeur date aussi de 1982, alors quel âges avaient vos parents en 1982 ? The Ninja Low Taper Fade meme is a viral internet trend that humorously reimagines professional gamer and streamer Tyler “Ninja” Blevins with a “low taper fade,” a popular hairstyle featuring a gradual fade starting low on the head and blending seamlessly into the skin. Known for his vibrant, dyed hair and clean-cut gamer aesthetic, Ninja is humorously transformed in the meme into a more urban or “street” persona, creating a comedic clash with his family-friendly and suburban image. As of 2024, the meme remains massive and continues to circulate widely, with new iterations and variations emerging regularly. Meta just invented artificial fingers (the digital fashion use case is wild). The project is called Digit360. Those little lights are super advanced digital fingertips. They pick up over 18 different attributes and can sense/react just like a human or animal would. For example, when it picks up something delicate, it knows how to adjust pressure to hold it carefully without breaking. Or if it feels something pointy, it can recoil immediately. But the coolest use case they teased was the future of digital fashion. In theory, a Digit360 scanner could be run across clothing and immediately be able to transmit the feeling of that material digitally. This means that brands could have mixed reality experiences where a user wearing haptic gloves could actually feel the texture, thickness, and quality of a garment from their couch. This is a bit of a futuristic example, but hints at where this is headed. Digit360 could also be super powerful if appended to the end of prosthetics, potentially giving more acute sensory feedback. Meta is currently working to scale the manufacturing of Digit360...I could see this giving way to an entirely new set of embodied experiences. 周函德 sent an attachment.
The tech in the Vegas Sphere is mindblowing... And it turns out, the screen (biggest ever created), is the least impressive part of the venue. The most impressive part, is the audio...it’s the most advanced sound system ever built. Inside the Sphere, there are 167,000 speakers hidden behind the screen. That’s 8 speakers per person. And this allows them to use Beam Forming technology to produce custom sound for each seat. This means they could play music in English for one section and music in Spanish for another section at the same time. Completely personalized sound...pretty nuts! The other thing that blew me away was the visuals. Not the screen specifically, moreso the camera. Turns out, the Sphere is so massive with such an extreme curvature, they had to invent the world’s most powerful video camera just to film for it. They call it, The Big Sky. It has a 165 degree field of view and shoots in 18K. 1 second of footage takes up 60GB of storage. They even had to build a secret mini sphere in California just to have somewhere to test how footage would look before it went into production. Overall, the project cost $2.3B and zero expense was spared. The second Sphere is under contract for Abu Dhabi and set to begin next year...I bet we see 10 of these by 2035. Also, shoutout to YouTube channels Megabuilds and Jacob Owen for making these insane visuals. I love finding cool tech/AI and helping share it to others. If you want me to make a video about your product/experience, drop me a message. If you run a tech company and want to teach your team how to make videos like me, I put together a free guide breaking down how I do it. Comment “viral” and I’ll send it. #tech #technology #sphere #lasvegas #lasvegasstrip #ai #artificialintelligence #concert #venue

The Chinese government's efforts to erase the memory of the Tiananmen Square Massacre are extensive and multifaceted. Since the tragic events of June 4, 1989, when the Chinese military violently suppressed pro-democracy protests, the government has consistently sought to censor any discussion or commemoration of the massacre. This includes imprisoning individuals in China and Hong Kong who attempt to honor the victims or acknowledge the event. The government has refused to take responsibility for the killings or provide redress to victims' families. Censorship is rigorously enforced through China's "Great Firewall," which blocks mentions of the massacre online. Social media platforms like Sina Weibo are heavily monitored, with posts related to Tiananmen being swiftly removed. In addition to online censorship, the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) has cultivated a form of cultural amnesia around the massacre. The event is not taught in schools, nor is it mentioned in official media outlets. As a result, many young people in China remain unaware of this significant historical event. The CCP's strategy has been to maintain its grip on power by suppressing political rights and controlling historical narratives. This approach has also been extended to Hong Kong, where authorities have removed books about the massacre from libraries and restricted public commemorations. Despite these efforts, the memory of Tiananmen persists among Chinese communities abroad and through international initiatives. For instance, the June 4 Memorial Museum in New York City serves as a permanent exhibition dedicated to preserving the history of the massacre and supporting pro-democracy movements. These global efforts highlight a continued resistance against Beijing's attempts to rewrite history and ensure that the legacy of Tiananmen remains alive outside China's borders. Sources: https://www.hrw.org/news/2024/06/02/china-closing-memory-tiananmen-massacre https://time.com/5571372/tiananmen-massacre-june-4-1989-china-censorship/ https://www.dailysignal.com/2024/06/04/35-years-after-tiananmen-square-beijing-still-tries-to-erase-memories/

The Dodge Challenger SRT Hellcat is where tires go to die. It’s one of the last coupes with American-style V-8 thunder under its hood. The Challenger SRT Hellcat lineup’s most reserved model spews 717 horsepower from its supercharged 6.2-liter V-8 engine. But there’s so much more: output from the Hellcat Redeye model’s version of this engine jumps to 797 horsepower. And the meanest, nastiest Hellcat Redeye, the Widebody Jailbreak edition, deploys 807 horsepower. All Challenger SRT Hellcats help you toward a suspended license with either a six-speed manual or an eight-speed automatic transmission; rear-wheel-drive is the only configuration offered and is one that is always ready to deploy billows of smoke from each of its massive, 12-inch-wide rear tires. While souped-up rivals such as the Chevy Camaro ZL1 and Ford Mustang Shelby GT500 are more road-course friendly, the SRT Hellcat has surface-prepared drag strip energy. And a lot of it. The more everyday all-wheel drive, V-6, and smaller V-8 equipped Challenger are reviewed separately. Dodge is gearing up for the final model year for the current generation Challenger SRT Hellcat by making the 807-hp Jailbreak package available on both the Redeye and non-Redeye models. All 2023 Challengers will come with a special “Last Call” plaque under the hood to commemorate the final production run before Dodge switches to a new generation of performance cars featuring electrified powertrains. The price of the 2023 Dodge Challenger SRT / SRT Hellcat starts at $71,895 and goes up to $92,895 depending on the trim and options. The Widebody version looks cooler with its flared fenders and handles better, thanks largely to wider wheels and tires, so that's the one we'd choose. Despite the fact that the SRT Hellcat is all about excess, we wouldn't opt for the Redeye model that increases power to nearly 800 horses. In fact, during our testing, the Redeye wasn't quicker than the standard Hellcat because its tires simply couldn't put the extra grunt to the ground.

周函德 sent an attachment.
Magnetic forces, like all electromagnetic forces, propagate at the speed of light, meaning that changes in a magnetic field can travel through space almost instantaneously on a human scale. However, when these forces interact with physical objects, the effect is not immediate acceleration to high velocities. Instead, objects respond to these forces gradually, in accordance with Newton’s second law of motion. This law states that the acceleration of an object is proportional to the force applied and inversely proportional to its mass. Therefore, even though the magnetic influence reaches the object almost instantly, the object itself accelerates slowly depending on the magnitude of the force and its own inertia. This interplay between the rapid propagation of electromagnetic forces and the gradual response of material objects reflects the fundamental principles of physics governing motion and force. Follow @spacecameocommunity for more. #magnetism #electromagnetic #physics #sciencefun #science

Nissan is a Japanese multinational automobile manufacturer headquartered in Yokohama, Japan. Founded in 1933, Nissan has grown to become one of the largest and most well-known car brands globally. The company is renowned for its innovative approach to automotive design and technology. Nissan offers a wide range of vehicles, from compact cars and sedans to SUVs, trucks, and electric vehicles. One of its most famous models is the Nissan Leaf, a pioneering electric vehicle that has gained popularity for its affordability and eco-friendly features. Nissan is also known for its performance-oriented cars, such as the Nissan GT-R, which has a strong reputation in the sports car market. The brand emphasizes safety, incorporating advanced features like ProPILOT Assist, an autonomous driving technology, in many of its models. Overall, Nissan combines reliability, cutting-edge technology, and a diverse lineup of vehicles to cater to a broad spectrum of consumers

The Tesla Cybertruck is an innovative and highly anticipated vehicle that has garnered significant attention for its unique design and advanced features. Its angular, futuristic exterior made of ultra-hard 30X cold-rolled stainless steel provides exceptional durability and strength, making it virtually bulletproof against small firearms. The Cybertruck boasts impressive performance with its tri-motor all-wheel drive variant, offering up to 500 miles of range on a single charge, rapid acceleration from 0 to 60 mph in under 2.9 seconds, and a towing capacity of over 14,000 pounds. Inside, the Cybertruck features a minimalist design with seating for up to six people, a 17-inch touchscreen display, and ample storage space. Its combination of rugged capability, cutting-edge technology, and sustainable electric power makes the Cybertruck a standout option in the electric vehicle market.

The Tesla Cybertruck is an all-electric pickup truck that was unveiled by Tesla, Inc. Here are some key details about the vehicle: Design • Exterior: The Cybertruck features a unique, futuristic design with a stainless steel exoskeleton. The angular, minimalist design sets it apart from traditional pickup trucks. • Glass: It uses Tesla’s “Armor Glass,” which is designed to be shatter-resistant. Performance • Variants: There are three versions: • Single Motor RWD (Rear-Wheel Drive) • Dual Motor AWD (All-Wheel Drive) • Tri Motor AWD (All-Wheel Drive) • Acceleration: The Tri Motor AWD version can accelerate from 0 to 60 mph in about 2.9 seconds. • Top Speed: Varies by model, with the Tri Motor AWD reaching up to 130 mph. Range and Battery • Range: The range also varies by model: • Single Motor RWD: Up to 250 miles • Dual Motor AWD: Up to 300 miles • Tri Motor AWD: Up to 500 miles • Battery: Equipped with a high-capacity battery pack to support these ranges. Towing and Payload • Towing Capacity: Up to 14,000 pounds (for the Tri Motor AWD version). • Payload Capacity: Up to 3,500 pounds. Interior and Features • Seating: The Cybertruck can seat up to six people. • Dashboard: Features a minimalist dashboard with a large touchscreen interface. • Autopilot: Comes with Tesla’s Autopilot as a standard feature, with full self-driving capability available as an upgrade. • Storage: Offers a 100 cubic feet of exterior, lockable storage including the under-bed, frunk, and sail pillars. Price • Starting Prices: • Single Motor RWD: $39,900 • Dual Motor AWD: $49,900 • Tri Motor AWD: $69,900 Production • Release Date: Initially planned for 2021, but production has faced delays. As of now, deliveries are expected to start in 2023.

What’s going on at the Polish McDonald’s😭🙏 #memesdaily #fyp #explorepage #meme #entertainment #trending #viral #relatable —- The Tesla Cybertruck is one of the most anticipated electric vehicles, standing out for its futuristic design, impressive performance, and advanced technology. Below is a comprehensive overview of its key features and specifications: Design and Exterior • Exoskeleton: The Cybertruck features an ultra-hard 30X cold-rolled stainless-steel exoskeleton. This material is designed to be nearly impenetrable, providing both durability and protection against dents, damage, and corrosion. • Armored Glass: Tesla introduced its “Tesla Armor Glass,” which is an ultra-strong glass and polymer-layered composite. It’s designed to absorb and redirect impact forces, further protecting the vehicle and its occupants. • Geometric Design: The vehicle has a unique, angular design that distinguishes it from traditional trucks. The sharp, geometric lines are not just for aesthetics but also contribute to the vehicle’s structural integrity. Performance • Powertrain Options: The Cybertruck is available in multiple configurations: • Single Motor RWD: The base model with rear-wheel drive (RWD). • Dual Motor AWD: A mid-tier option with all-wheel drive (AWD). • Tri-Motor AWD: The top-tier model with three electric motors and all-wheel drive. • Acceleration: • The Tri-Motor AWD can accelerate from 0-60 mph in approximately 2.9 seconds. • The Dual Motor AWD takes about 4.5 seconds. • The Single Motor RWD is slightly slower but still impressive at around 6.5 seconds. • Top Speed: Depending on the model, the top speed ranges from 110 mph (Single Motor) to 130 mph (Tri-Motor). Range and Battery • Range: • The Single Motor RWD version offers a range of over 250 miles per charge. • The Dual Motor AWD can go over 300 miles. • The Tri-Motor AWD boasts a range exceeding 500 miles on a single charge. • Charging: Tesla’s extensive Supercharger network can be utilized for fast charging. The Cybertruck is expected to support the latest V3 Superchargers, which can add up to 75 miles of range in just 5 minutes.

Here’s a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: ### Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed - 4 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks (optional) ### Instructions: 1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. **Melt Butter**: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. **Mix Sugars and Eggs**: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. **Combine Dry Ingredients**: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. **Add Chocolate Chips**: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. **Cool and Serve**: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving. Enjoy your homemade brownies! . . #reel #reach #viral #instagram #explorepage #explore #trending #viralreels #memesdaily #meme #memepage #foryoupage #fyp

Did you know that there's a place on Earth where gravity is weaker? 🌍🔍 At Mount Nevado Huascarán in Peru, gravity is slightly weaker than in most other places due to its location near the equator and its high altitude. This phenomenon occurs because the planet bulges at the equator, meaning you're farther from the planet's core.

The LaFerrari, officially known as the Ferrari LaFerrari, is a hybrid sports car manufactured by Ferrari. It was produced from 2013 to 2016 as the successor to the Enzo Ferrari. Here are some key details about the LaFerrari: 1. **Performance**: It features a 6.3-liter V12 engine combined with an electric motor, producing a combined output of around 950 horsepower. This setup allows the LaFerrari to accelerate from 0 to 60 mph (0 to 100 km/h) in under 3 seconds and achieve a top speed of over 217 mph (350 km/h). 2. **Hybrid System**: The LaFerrari incorporates Ferrari’s HY-KERS hybrid system, which enhances performance while improving fuel efficiency and reducing emissions. The electric motor assists the internal combustion engine during acceleration and also allows for electric-only driving at low speeds. 3. **Design**: Its design is highly aerodynamic and focused on maximizing downforce and minimizing drag. The LaFerrari’s styling reflects Ferrari’s commitment to both performance and aesthetics, with sharp lines and a low-slung profile. 4. **Limited Production**: Only 499 units were produced, making it a highly exclusive and sought-after vehicle among collectors and enthusiasts. Each LaFerrari was hand-built and customized to some extent according to the buyer’s preferences. 5. **Technological Features**: It incorporates advanced technologies such as active aerodynamics, adaptive suspension, and extensive use of lightweight materials like carbon fiber to optimize performance and handling. Overall, the LaFerrari represents Ferrari’s pinnacle of automotive engineering and performance, blending traditional V12 power with modern hybrid technology to create a hypercar that delivers exhilarating performance on both the road and the track.

recipe of the day 👇 Sticky Toffee Pudding **Ingredients:** **For the pudding:** - 200g dates, pitted and chopped - 300ml boiling water - 1 teaspoon baking soda - 85g unsalted butter, softened - 175g light brown sugar - 2 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 200g self-raising flour - 1 teaspoon baking powder **For the toffee sauce:** - 200g light brown sugar - 100g unsalted butter - 300ml double cream - 1 tablespoon black treacle or golden syrup **Instructions:** 1. **Prepare the dates:** Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F). Grease and line an 8-inch square baking dish. Place the chopped dates in a bowl, pour over the boiling water, and stir in the baking soda. Let it sit while you prepare the pudding batter. 2. **Make the batter:** In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time, then add the vanilla extract. Sift in the flour and baking powder, then gently fold in the soaked dates and their liquid. 3. **Bake the pudding:** Pour the batter into the prepared baking dish and bake for 35-40 minutes, or until a skewer inserted into the center comes out clean. 4. **Make the toffee sauce:** While the pudding is baking, make the sauce. In a saucepan, combine the sugar, butter, cream, and treacle (or golden syrup). Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the sugar has dissolved. Bring to a simmer and cook for 3-4 minutes until thickened slightly. 5. **Serve:** Once the pudding is done, poke holes all over the surface with a skewer or fork, and pour half of the toffee sauce over the top. Allow it to soak in for a few minutes. Serve warm, drizzled with the remaining sauce, and enjoy with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or whipped cream! Enjoy this rich and indulgent dessert!

follow @ssd.memes for more - Here’s a simple and delicious chocolate chip cookie recipe for you: **Ingredients:** - 1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, softened - 1 cup white sugar - 1 cup packed brown sugar - 2 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 3 cups all-purpose flour - 1 teaspoon baking soda - 1/2 teaspoon baking powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 2 cups semisweet chocolate chips **Instructions:** 1. Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar until smooth. 3. Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla. 4. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. Gradually add this dry mixture to the wet ingredients, mixing until just blended. 5. Stir in the chocolate chips. 6. Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheet. 7. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in the preheated oven, or until the edges are golden brown. Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Enjoy your delicious homemade chocolate chip cookies!

Creamy Garlic Parmesan Pasta Ingredients: • 8 oz fettuccine • 2 tbsp butter • 4 cloves garlic, minced • 1 cup heavy cream • 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese • 1/2 cup chicken broth • Salt and pepper to taste • Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish) Instructions: 1. Cook the fettuccine according to package instructions. Drain and set aside. 2. In a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the minced garlic and sauté for 1-2 minutes until fragrant, but not browned. 3. Pour in the heavy cream and chicken broth, stirring to combine. Bring the mixture to a simmer. 4. Gradually whisk in the grated Parmesan cheese until the sauce is smooth and creamy. Season with salt and pepper to taste. 5. Add the cooked fettuccine to the skillet, tossing to coat the pasta evenly with the sauce. 6. Allow the pasta to simmer in the sauce for 2-3 minutes, letting the flavors meld together. 7. Serve immediately, garnished with chopped fresh parsley. Enjoy your deliciously creamy garlic Parmesan pasta!

The Tesla Cybertruck is an all-electric, battery-powered light-duty truck unveiled by Tesla, Inc. Here’s a comprehensive overview of its key features and specifications: Tesla Cybertruck Overview Design and Structure • Exterior: The Cybertruck has a distinctive, angular, stainless steel exoskeleton design for durability and passenger protection. It features ultra-hard 30X cold-rolled stainless steel and armored glass. • Dimensions: Approximately 231.7 inches long, 79.8 inches wide, and 75 inches tall, with a 6.5-foot cargo bed. Performance and Variants • Single Motor RWD: ◦ 0-60 mph: ~6.5 seconds ◦ Range: ~250 miles ◦ Towing Capacity: 7,500 pounds • Dual Motor AWD: ◦ 0-60 mph: ~4.5 seconds ◦ Range: ~300 miles ◦ Towing Capacity: 10,000 pounds • Tri-Motor AWD: ◦ 0-60 mph: ~2.9 seconds ◦ Range: ~500 miles ◦ Towing Capacity: 14,000 pounds

inhaling helium can make your voice sound higher-pitched. This happens because helium is much lighter than air, allowing sound waves to travel faster through it. When you speak after inhaling helium, the faster vibration of your vocal cords changes the pitch of your voice, making it sound higher and squeakier. However, be careful not to inhale too much helium, as it can displace the oxygen you need to breathe, leading to dizziness or even fainting. Videos by : @_m7xyz #memes

The Tesla Cybertruck is a battery electric pickup truck built by Tesla, Inc. since 2023.[5] Introduced as a concept vehicle in November 2019, it has a body design reminiscent of low-polygon modelling, consisting of flat stainless steel sheet panels. Tesla Cybertruck Cybertruck in a parking lot (2024) Overview Manufacturer Tesla, Inc. Production November 2023 – present Assembly United States: Austin, Texas (Gigafactory Texas) Designer * Franz von Holzhausen Body and chassis Class Pickup truck Body style 4-door crew cab Layout * Rear motor, rear-wheel drive * Dual- or tri-motor, all-wheel drive Powertrain Transmission Single-speed fixed (15:1 ratio) Battery * 123 kWh lithium-ion (816 V, 150 Ah) * +50 kWh (optional range extender) Electric range * 250–340 mi (400–545 km) (EPA est.) * 440–470 mi (710–755 km) (with range extender) Plug-in charging * AC onboard charger: *     11.5 kW at 240 V, 48 A * DC: *     ≤250 kW at 400 V[1] *     ≤350 kW at 800 V[2] * NACS connector Dimensions Wheelbase 143.11 in (3,635 mm) Length 223.74 in (5,683 mm) Width 79.99 in (2,032 mm) Height 70.7 in (1,796 mm)[3] Curb weight * AWD: 6,603 lb (2,995 kg)[4] * Cyberbeast: 6,843 lb (3,104 kg)[4]

Hibernation is an adaptation for survival in harsh conditions like cold or food scarcity. Animals reduce metabolism, store fat, lower body temperature, slow breathing/heart rate, and seek insulated shelters. These mechanisms evolved to conserve energy and help animals endure tough times, emerging unharmed when conditions improve. Animals rely on stored energy, mainly fats, to endure food scarcity and harsh winters. Smaller mammals experience torpor, lowering body temperature with intermittent warming periods, while larger mammals maintain more stable temperatures. The Bugatti Chiron is a marvel of automotive engineering and luxury, representing the pinnacle of performance and craftsmanship from the iconic French manufacturer. Introduced in 2016 as the successor to the Veyron, the Chiron features an 8.0-liter quad-turbocharged W16 engine, producing a staggering 1,479 horsepower and 1,180 lb-ft of torque. This immense power allows the Chiron to reach speeds of up to 261 mph, with acceleration from 0 to 60 mph in just 2.4 seconds. The car's design is a blend of futuristic aesthetics and aerodynamic efficiency, with distinctive features such as the signature C-shaped side lines and a sleek, flowing body. Inside, the Chiron offers an opulent interior with top-tier materials and advanced technology, ensuring a driving experience that is both thrilling and luxurious. Limited to just 500 units, each Bugatti Chiron is a testament to the brand's dedication to pushing the boundaries of automotive excellence.

The Rolls-Royce Wraith is a luxury grand tourer introduced by Rolls-Royce in 2013. It is known for its combination of high performance, opulent features, and distinctive design. Here is a comprehensive overview of the Rolls-Royce Wraith: ### Design and Exterior - **Body Style**: The Wraith is a two-door coupe with a fastback design. - **Dimensions**: It measures about 207.9 inches in length, 76.7 inches in width, and 59.3 inches in height, with a wheelbase of 122.5 inches. - **Distinctive Features**: The Wraith features the iconic Rolls-Royce grille, coach doors (also known as suicide doors), and a sleek roofline that gives it a sporty yet elegant appearance. ### Engine and Performance - **Engine**: The Wraith is powered by a 6.6-liter twin-turbocharged V12 engine. - **Power Output**: It delivers around 624 horsepower and 605 lb-ft of torque. - **Transmission**: The engine is paired with an 8-speed automatic transmission. - **Performance**: The Wraith can accelerate from 0 to 60 mph in about 4.4 seconds, with a top speed electronically limited to 155 mph. ### Interior and Comfort - **Luxury Appointments**: The interior is handcrafted with the finest materials, including premium leather, wood veneers, and metal accents. - **Technology**: Features include a state-of-the-art infotainment system with a large central display, a bespoke audio system, and advanced navigation. - **Comfort**: The Wraith offers a spacious cabin with plush seating, a starlight headliner (fiber-optic lights embedded in the roof to resemble a starry night), and climate control. ### Driving Experience - **Ride Quality**: The Wraith is known for its smooth and quiet ride, thanks to its advanced suspension system and sound insulation. - **Handling**: Despite its size, the Wraith handles well, providing a comfortable yet engaging driving experience. ### Customization - **Bespoke Options**: Rolls-Royce offers extensive customization options, allowing buyers to personalize their Wraith with unique paint colors, interior trims, and bespoke features. - **Special Editions**: Over the years, there have been various special editions of the Wraith, featuring unique design elements and exclusive fin

Follow (me) @flawedjhit for more memes just like this! 🔥 - - - - - - - - Here’s a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: ### Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed - 4 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks (optional) ### Instructions: 1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. **Melt Butter**: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. **Mix Sugars and Eggs**: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. **Combine Dry Ingredients**: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. **Add Chocolate Chips**: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. **Cool and Serve**: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving. Enjoy your homemade brownies!

She’s 10 btw… Here’s a classic recipe for brownies that yields a rich, fudgy, and delicious dessert: Ingredients: · 1 and 1/2 sticks of unsalted butter (12 tablespoons), plus more for greasing the pan · 2 cups of sugar · 4 large eggs · 1/2 cup of unsweetened cocoa powder · 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract · 1 and 1/4 cups of all-purpose flour · 1 teaspoon of salt · 1 cup of semi-sweet chocolate chips · 1 cup of chopped walnuts (optional) Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 350°F (180°C). Grease an 8-inch square baking pan with butter and line it with parchment paper. 2. Melt the butter and sugar in a medium saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the butter is melted. 3. Remove the saucepan from the heat and stir in the cocoa powder until it’s well combined. 4. Let the mixture cool slightly, then stir in the eggs one at a time, followed by the vanilla extract. 5. In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour and salt. 6. Add the flour mixture to the saucepan and stir until just combined. 7. Stir in the chocolate chips and walnuts (if using). 8. Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and smooth the top. 9. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs. 10. Let the brownies cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving. Enjoy your delicious homemade brownies!

Literal brain rot To cook a tender steak, it’s crucial to start with a good quality piece of meat. Look for cuts that are well-marbled with fat, such as ribeye or New York strip. Before cooking, allow the steak to come to room temperature, as this ensures even cooking. Season the steak generously with salt and pepper, or your preferred steak seasoning, and let it sit for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to penetrate the meat. For the cooking process, preheat a heavy skillet or grill pan over high heat. The pan should be hot enough that it sizzles when you place the steak on it. Sear the steak for a few minutes on each side to create a caramelized crust. Then, reduce the heat to medium and continue cooking to your desired level of doneness. Use a meat thermometer to achieve the perfect temperature: 120°F for rare, 130°F for medium-rare, 140°F for medium, and so on. Remember to let the steak rest for a few minutes before slicing it, as this allows the juices to redistribute and results in a more tender and flavorful steak. Another method to ensure a tender steak is to marinate it before cooking. Create a marinade using ingredients like olive oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, and herbs. Place the steak in a resealable bag and pour the marinade over it, making sure it is evenly coated. Let it marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, or overnight for maximum flavor. When it’s time to cook, remove the steak from the marinade and pat it dry with paper towels. Discard the marinade as it may contain harmful bacteria. Preheat your grill or skillet over medium-high heat and cook the steak following the same searing and cooking instructions as mentioned before. The marinade not only adds flavor but also helps to tenderize the meat by breaking down the muscle fibers. By following these techniques, you can cook a steak that is not only delicious but also incredibly tender. Whether you choose to sear it or marinate it, remember that the key lies in using high-quality meat and giving it the proper time and attention it deserves. #reels #brainrot #dankmemes

No problem, here’s some information on the Mercedes-Benz CLR GTR is a notable racing car developed for the 1999 24 Hours of Le Mans by Mercedes-AMG. It was the successor to the successful CLK GTR and CLK LM models used in GT racing. The CLR GTR was designed with the goal of competing in the Le Mans Prototype (LMP) category, featuring a sleeker and more aerodynamic body than its predecessors. However, the CLR GTR is most famously remembered for its notorious incidents at the 1999 Le Mans race. During practice and the race itself, the CLR GTR experienced severe aerodynamic instability, leading to three separate instances where the car flipped into the air at high speeds. The most dramatic incident occurred during the race when driver Peter Dumbreck’s car flipped and went airborne, landing in the trees. Fortunately, no drivers were seriously injured in these incidents. The aerodynamic issues were primarily due to the car’s design, which created lift at high speeds, exacerbated by the undulating surface of the Le Mans circuit. These incidents led Mercedes-Benz to withdraw from the race and subsequently exit from Le Mans racing altogether for several years. Despite its advanced engineering and high potential, the CLR GTR is often remembered as a cautionary tale about the importance of aerodynamic stability in race car design. #meme #dark #darkmeme #jokesonyou #repost #edit #video #comments #trending #trendingvideos #humour #darkhumour #lilbro #fyp #💀

classic String theory is a theoretical framework in physics that aims to reconcile general relativity and quantum mechanics, the two pillars of modern physics. At its core, string theory proposes that the fundamental building blocks of the universe are not point-like particles, but rather one-dimensional “strings” that vibrate at specific frequencies. These vibrations determine the properties of particles, such as mass and charge, much like the different notes produced by a vibrating guitar string 🎸. One of the most intriguing aspects of string theory is its requirement for additional dimensions beyond the familiar three dimensions of space and one dimension of time. In fact, string theory suggests the existence of up to 11 dimensions! These extra dimensions are thought to be compactified or curled up so small that they are not easily observable in our everyday experience 🌀. String theory has also given rise to the concept of “branes,” multi-dimensional objects on which strings can attach. Our entire universe could be a 3-dimensional brane floating in a higher-dimensional space, with other branes potentially hosting parallel universes 🪐. Despite its elegance and potential, string theory remains highly speculative. It has yet to produce testable predictions that can be experimentally verified. Nonetheless, it offers a tantalizing glimpse into the deeper structure of reality and continues to inspire physicists in their quest for a unified theory of everything. Whether or not string theory ultimately proves correct, its influence on theoretical physics and the way we think about the universe is undeniable. 🌌✨

Here’s a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: ### Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed - 4 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks Instructions: 1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. **Melt Butter**: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. **Mix Sugars and Eggs**: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. **Combine Dry Ingredients**: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. **Add Chocolate Chips**: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. **Cool and Serve**: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving.

follow me @weakmemes.v1 for more 😂 Classic Pancakes Ingredients: - 1 cup all-purpose flour - 2 tablespoons sugar - 1 teaspoon baking powder - 1/2 teaspoon baking soda - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 3/4 cup buttermilk - 1/4 cup milk - 1 large egg - 2 tablespoons melted butter - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - Butter or oil for cooking #### Instructions: 1. Mix Dry Ingredients: In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. 2. Combine Wet Ingredients: In another bowl, mix the buttermilk, milk, egg, melted butter, and vanilla extract until well combined. 3. Combine Mixtures: Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and gently stir until just combined. Be careful not to overmix; some lumps are okay. 4. Preheat Griddle: Heat a non-stick griddle or large skillet over medium heat. Lightly grease with butter or oil. 5. Cook Pancakes: Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto the griddle for each pancake. Cook until bubbles form on the surface and the edges look set, then flip and cook until golden brown on the other side. 6. Serve: Serve warm with your favorite toppings like maple syrup, fresh berries, or whipped cream. Enjoy your fluffy, delicious pancakes!

Here’s a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed - 4 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks (optional) Instructions: 1. Preheat Oven: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. Melt Butter: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. Mix Sugars and Eggs: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. Combine Dry Ingredients: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. Add Chocolate Chips: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. Bake: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. Cool and Serve: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving. Enjoy your homemade brownies!

shocking String theory is a theoretical framework in which the point-like particles of particle physics are replaced by one-dimensional objects known as strings. These strings can vibrate at different frequencies, and their different vibrational modes are thought to correspond to the various fundamental particles observed in nature. This idea emerged in the late 20th century as physicists sought to reconcile general relativity, which describes gravity at macroscopic scales, with quantum mechanics, which explains the behavior of particles at microscopic scales. One of the most compelling features of string theory is its potential to unify all the fundamental forces of nature—gravitational, electromagnetic, strong, and weak interactions—into a single theoretical framework. This has led some to dub it a “theory of everything” 🌌. In addition, string theory requires extra spatial dimensions beyond the familiar three. These additional dimensions are theorized to be compactified or curled up in such a way that they are not observable at everyday energy scales. String theory also introduces the concept of supersymmetry, a proposed symmetry between bosons and fermions. This theoretical symmetry could solve many puzzles in particle physics and cosmology, including the hierarchy problem and the nature of dark matter. Despite its elegance and mathematical beauty, string theory remains a topic of active research and debate within the scientific community due to the current lack of experimental evidence 🧩. The development and exploration of string theory continue to push the boundaries of our understanding of the universe, offering tantalizing possibilities for a more profound comprehension of the cosmos and its underlying principles ✨.

Here’s a condensed version of the recipe to make KFC-style fried chicken at home: Ingredients: 1 whole chicken, cut into pieces 2 cups all-purpose flour 2 tablespoons cornstarch 1 tablespoon salt 1 tablespoon black pepper 1 tablespoon paprika 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon onion powder 1 teaspoon dried thyme 1 teaspoon dried oregano 1 teaspoon dried basil 1 teaspoon celery salt 1 teaspoon dried mustard powder 1 teaspoon ground ginger 2 cups buttermilk (or mix 2 cups milk with 2 tbsp vinegar or lemon juice) Vegetable oil for frying Instructions: Marinate the Chicken: Mix buttermilk with 1 tbsp salt in a bowl. Add chicken, coat well. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Prepare Breading: Mix flour, cornstarch, and all spices in another bowl. Coat the Chicken: Remove chicken from marinade, let excess drip off. Coat chicken pieces thoroughly in flour mixture. Fry the Chicken: Heat oil to 350°F (175°C) in a pot. Fry chicken pieces until golden brown and cooked through, about 15-20 minutes. Drain on paper towels. Serve: Let chicken rest briefly. Serve hot with sides like mashed potatoes and coleslaw. The biggest culture shocks when I got home ⬇️ [Hi, I’m Julianne. Left the U.S. to study abroad in May 2023 and have been to 22 countries since. Follow along @journalofjulianne for more relatable study abroad content] So back to what surprised me… Everything is HUGE. From the take out cups to cars it feels like everything grew in size after crossing the Atlantic. The prices aren’t as bad as I thought they would be. I mean some things are more expensive (beer, wine) but it wasn’t as bad as I thought after spending a year away. Atlanta is full of trees. Like, a lot of trees. I never realized just how much forest coverage we have everywhere. It makes Spain look like a desert. American coins feel like I could snap them in two- they’re so light compared to the Euro and I only need 4 quarters to make a dollar instead of 5 20¢ coins to make a Euro so I keep getting that wrong. #summerinternship #internabroad #studyabroad #erasmusgeneration #americaninspain #costco #americanculture

Peter 💀 Follow @daily_griffin_clips_ for daily dose of laughter The Great Blue Hole in Belize is one of the most fascinating natural wonders on Earth. Located about 70 kilometers (43 miles) from the mainland and Belize City, this giant marine sinkhole is a part of the Lighthouse Reef, a small atoll that is part of the larger Belize Barrier Reef Reserve System, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The Blue Hole is almost perfectly circular, with a diameter of over 300 meters (984 feet) and a depth of 125 meters (410 feet). The sinkhole was formed during several episodes of quaternary glaciation when sea levels were much lower. As the sea levels rose, the caves were flooded, creating the Blue Hole we see today. Its deep blue color stands in stark contrast to the lighter, turquoise waters of the surrounding shallow reefs, creating a dramatic and visually striking phenomenon. The Great Blue Hole is a mecca for scuba divers, who come from all over the world to explore its depths. Divers are drawn to the crystal-clear waters, the impressive stalactites and stalagmites that can be found at depths of 30 meters (100 feet) and deeper, and the diverse marine life that inhabits the area. Species such as nurse sharks, giant groupers, and various types of reef sharks, including the Caribbean reef shark, can be found within the Blue Hole. In addition to its natural beauty, the Blue Hole has significant scientific value. It offers researchers insights into the geological and climatic history of the region, as the stalactites and stalagmites provide clues about the Earth's past sea levels and climate conditions. The formations found within the sinkhole suggest that it was once a dry cave system, now submerged due to rising sea levels. #familyguy #petergriffin #stewiegriffin #funnyshit #explorepageready #explorepage #lmao😂😂😂 #laughoutloud #funnyclips #funnyvideos#comedyvideos #comedyvideo #comedymemes #familyguymemes #dankmemesdaily #dankvideos #humourous #hahaha #meggriffin

Please follow I'm poor😭 . . . . Sure, here's a simple recipe for homemade chocolate fudge: ### Ingredients: - 2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips - 1 (14-ounce) can sweetened condensed milk - 1/4 cup unsalted butter - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - Pinch of salt - Optional: 1/2 cup chopped nuts (like walnuts or pecans) ### Instructions: 1. **Prepare the Pan**: Line an 8-inch square baking pan with parchment paper or aluminum foil, leaving some overhang on the sides. This will make it easier to lift the fudge out later. 2. **Melt the Ingredients**: In a medium saucepan over low heat, combine the chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk, and butter. Stir constantly until the chocolate and butter are completely melted and the mixture is smooth. 3. **Add Vanilla and Salt**: Remove the saucepan from the heat and stir in the vanilla extract and a pinch of salt. If you are adding nuts, fold them in at this point. 4. **Pour into Pan**: Pour the fudge mixture into the prepared pan, spreading it out evenly with a spatula. 5. **Chill**: Let the fudge cool to room temperature, then refrigerate it for at least 2 hours or until it is firm. 6. **Cut and Serve**: Lift the fudge out of the pan using the parchment paper overhang. Cut it into small squares with a sharp knife. ### Tips: - For a different flavor, you can add a teaspoon of instant coffee granules to the mixture while melting. - For a festive touch, sprinkle crushed peppermint candies or sea salt on top of the fudge before it sets. Enjoy your homemade chocolate fudge! #funny #viral #fyp #brainrot #global

Visualisation of how Convolutional Neural Network works. A Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) operates by applying filters to input data, extracting features through convolution and pooling layers. These filters systematically scan the input, detecting patterns like edges. The network learns these filters during training, enabling it to recognize complex features in images. By combining convolution and pooling layers, CNNs create feature maps that highlight detected features. This process allows CNNs to excel in image and video analysis, offering robustness to variations like translation and rotation. #ai #artificialintelligence #machinelearning #technology #tech #india #programming #coding #datascience #iot #deeplearning #code #robotics #future #bigdata #programmer #python #business #startup #entrepreneur #automation #innovation #instagood #data #science #life #picoftheday #love #illustration #ml

Stand under for some comp😭 - Scoob The NSX is a high-performance sports car produced by Honda under its luxury brand, Acura. It is a mid-engine, all-wheel-drive supercar that combines cutting-edge technology, exceptional performance, and stylish design. The exterior design of the NSX is characterized by sleek and aerodynamic lines, with a low and wide stance that exudes a sense of speed and agility. It features sharp edges and bold curves that enhance its modern and aggressive look. The car is built using lightweight materials such as aluminum and carbon fiber, which contribute to its overall performance and handling. Underneath the hood, the NSX is powered by a hybrid powertrain. It combines a twin-turbocharged V6 engine with three electric motors. The V6 engine is positioned in the middle of the car, providing a low center of gravity and optimal weight distribution. The electric motors assist the engine, providing instant torque and enhancing acceleration.

This is real btw - The Mercedes-Benz CLK GTR is a rare hypercar that began as a race car and was developed to compete with the Porsche 911 GT1 and McLaren F1 GTR in the FIA GT Championship. The CLK GTR debuted at the 1997 FIA GT Hockenheim 4 Hours, where Bernd Schneider qualified on pole but had to retire due to braking problems. The CLK GTR won back-to-back FIA GT Championships in 1997 and 1998, and at the time of its release in 1998, Guinness World Records named the CLK GTR Straßenversion and its siblings the world’s most expensive production cars. In 2021, the CLK GTR Straßenversion retailed for $2,572,940, which was the record until the introduction of the Ferrari FXX-K in 2015.

This is not what I asked for #darkhumor #funny #dankmemes #darkmemes #toystory #explorepage #memepage #memes Here’s a pizza recipe to make longer captions * Get a good pizza pan. The key to a good crust is a good pizza pan. You want one that will cook the crust evenly on all sides, including the bottom. Lots of cooks swear by a pizza stone. To use a pizza stone, preheat it in the oven (on the “stone” setting if you have a Wolf oven) while you stretch and top your dough. Then, quickly slide the assembled pizza onto the stone and transfer both to the oven to bake. The hot stone will help your crust get nice & crisp on the bottom. * Keep your dough covered. As your homemade pizza dough rises, make sure to keep it covered. You want to lock moisture in with the dough to keep it soft & pliable. Otherwise, a crusty film will develop around the dough ball, and it will dry out and lose its flexibility. * Bake, then garnish! Fresh, delicate toppings like herbs will wilt and lose their flavor in the hot oven, so top them onto your pie right before serving. Along with the fresh basil & mint, I like to add dollops of pesto and a drizzle of olive oil before sitting down to eat. With a good whole grain crust and lots of veggie toppings, homemade pizza is a filling meal on its own. If we want something on the side, though, my first choice is always a seasonal salad. A simple green salad or arugula salad is an easy, fresh option, but if I’m not tossing greens together, I’ll often use leftover pizza toppings to make a fun, flavorful side salad. Here are some of my favorite salads that make use of toppings that you may have leftover from this homemade pizza recipe:

Jeff Permar, a gardener in Delaware, noticed someone stealing his veggies in 2019. So, he set up a camera, and caught a groundhog munching on his vegetables. Finding it amusing, Jeff decided to befriend the groundhog and named him “Chunk.” While Jeff tended to his own garden, he created another one accessible to Chunk. The groundhog soon attracted a partner named Nibbles, for whom Jeff even built a picnic table. As Chunk and Nibbles’ family grew to five, including their children Nugget, Chip, and Chibbles, Jeff eagerly awaited their emergence from hibernation in February. With Chunk’s family expanding, Jeff learned to distinguish each member by unique traits and shared his harvest with them. He now sees Chunk as the leader, estimating his age at six, and recognizing Chunk Jr.’s emerging leadership. Jeff also interacted with Snacks, a member of the groundhog family who had dental issues, showing his care for all members. Over time, Jeff’s garden became a shared feast, bringing together man and groundhog. 🎥 Jeff Permar

What’s your screen time? Credit: @mory.q Master Your Screen Time, Unlock Your Potential, Not Your Phone. In our digitally dominated realm, the smartphone is a double-edged sword. Expert testimony to Congress by Justin unveils an unsettling truth: our innate impulses are often hijacked by meticulously engineered algorithms, leading us down a rabbit hole of endless scrolling. However, this narrative isn’t about demonizing technology, but shedding light on achieving a disciplined and mindful engagement with our devices. Your phone can be a potent tool for personal growth and life enrichment when used judiciously. It can nourish your mind, connect you with loved ones, and even foster new skills. The onus is on us to utilize this powerful tool to fuel our ambitions rather than letting it drain our precious time. Mindful usage starts with awareness, followed by disciplined action. Embrace apps that foster productivity, learning, and genuine connection. Set boundaries, like specific times for social media engagement or using screen time trackers to stay accountable. Remember, the power to use technology for our advantage lies within us. It’s about making intentional choices that align with our life’s aspirations. 周函德 sent an attachment.
The copper provides an initial path to ground for the electricity, and because the voltage is so high (on the order of a hundred thousand) that the copper vaporizes almost instantly. The copper and the air around it are ionized by the heat, making the air itself conductive. This can happen spontaneously in the case of lightning or other arcing if the voltage is high enough or the gap is small enough (the breakdown voltage of dry air is something like 10,000 volts per centimeter). The power line is engineered such that everything has enough separation distance to prevent this, but the copper bridges the gap. What you see is Plasma, the fourth state of matter. Plasma is an ionized gas consisting of approximately equal numbers of positively and negatively charged particles. Additionally, the lightning seen in thunderstorms is another form of plasma. Lightning is caused by electricity traveling through the air and ionizing the areas it travels through, creating a great conductor path.
